INVALID on 19/07/2018 (11:20 am) we began looking for the net. We were not able to locate any flags, buoys, or nets. We used sonar, visual observation, and dragging an anchor like a hook to try and find the net with no success. We stopped searching at 12:30. we will report the net missing and return tomorrow to continue looking. net possibly sank or was removed by another party (fisheries officer or fisherman?) - JB / 20/7/2018 we found the net about 1.5 km SW of the grid (the crew likely drifted when setting on 18/07/2018). all LKWF that were of good quality were kept as well as all LKT and INCO. Total time net was in the water was ~52 hours. As it is an invalid set time, the fish number, species, etc. were not recorded. There were lots of fish in the nets and the nets need to be looked over and repaired - JB crew Roland, PS, WS
